args: If I'm going to try and make friends here,\nI need to find someone a bit closer\nto my own energy level.
Guys like that skater and dancer are\nmore of a deep-end-of-the-pool thing.
So who looks easy to get along with and\nlaid-back enough to handle? Hmm...
Hmm? You want me to look over there?
Huh. Yeah, okay. He looks close to my age\nand seems pretty quiet. Might work.
Thanks for the heads up, Sam.\nI'm gonna go talk to him!
I hope this works so I can finally have\nsome NORMAL teen years.
(I did it! I managed to say hello\nwithout being all weird about it!)
Oh, hello. Are you one of the\nprince's new recruits?
Er, yeah. My name is...um...it's Eugene.\nNice to meet you.
Oh, likewise. I'm Nicolas, a student\nfrom the Caldia Magic Academy.
(Damn, he must be really smart.\nHow am I supposed to make friends\nwith a huge brain like that?)
Nothing just wanted to say hi and I\ndid so now I'm saying bye. So...bye.
Man, there really are some amazing\npeople around this place.
A young priest in training? Well, he seems\npretty normal—might as well give it a try.
All right! Priest work done for the day!\nWhich means it's time fooooor...
Knight training! Oh yeah, let's WORK it!
Or he's a knight. A priest-knight.\nWait, is that even a thing?
No I'm just leaving gotta go bye.
Man, what is UP with this castle?\nEveryone's either a complete weirdo\nor a world-class genius.
Yeah, you're right, Sam—\nit's too early to give up yet.
There's a zillion people in this castle,\nso there's gotta be at least ONE who\ngets my general...deal.
I can't do this any more. I'm exhausted.
Looks like I'm doomed to be as alone here\nas I am at home. So much for the stupid\ndream of making a stupid friend, gosh!
But at least I've got you, Sam.
We can still play games together,\nso it's not like I'm totally alone.
Hey, you're that guy from earlier!\nOh, is that a board game? Nice.
I used to play board games with the other\nvillage kids back at my parents' church.
This one can take four players, yeah?\nYou mind if I find a couple other folks\nand we all join in?
(Well, THIS got out of hand quick.)
Let me see... I rolled a nine, so I'm going\nto move my heavy cavalry.
Mmm... Then I shall intercept using two of\nmy light infantry together.
Everyone's so good at this—\nit's really anyone's game!
(Great. I'm surrounded by a child genius,\na ninja assassin, and a priest-knight.)
(I couldn't stand out more if I tried.)
I look forward to seeing how you will\nendeavor to break this stalemate.
Yes, this move will likely determine\nthe course of the entire battle!
Ha ha! I can't wait to see where this goes!
(I had no idea this game could be\nso great with other people!)
All right, I rolled a 10, so I'm going to\nmove my shock trooper forward!
Missed my shield knight, did you?
Crap! It's going to repel my attacks\nand create an opening!
(I got so carried away by having fun\nthat I let my strategy suffer!)
Time to mount a counterattack.\nI'm gonna plow into Eugene's ranks!
Though it pains me to double down on a\ndefeated foe, I'm going to do the same.
There is no place for mercy in war.\nPrepare to meet your end at my hand.
Oh man, I'm deep in it now!
(Urgh... Why am I always making critical\nmistakes at the very worst times?)
(...No, he's right. It's too early to give up.)
(After playing so much with Sam,\nI know everything there is to know\nabout this game!)
(There has to be some way to turn\nmy fate around. Lemme see...)
Ah! If I move my shock trooper there...
Running away, eh? Big mistake!\nYou'll be cornered before you know it!
Oh, I'm not running away.\nI'm preparing to win.
Shock troopers get a special terrain bonus\nwhen they fight on a hill.
Their charge power doubles when moving\ndown steep slopes—which means I can\nroll twice the usual number of dice!
Yes! That's a 20! Charge, shock trooper!\nMow down everything in your path!
Yessss! All three of your commanders\nare down, which means I win!
Whoooooa. How did you plan all that?!
Astounding. The cornered jackal\ntruly is the most dangerous game.
I had a lot of fun, even though I got\ncompletely annihilated.
Me, too! Let's play again sometime,\nEugene! Sound good?
I'm fine, buddy. That just wore me out\na bit.
Still, that's the first time anyone's\never asked to play with me again.
I'm really glad I came back here.\nThanks for giving me the push, Sam.
